# Numen UI Design Track ‚Äî rules for this worktree

This worktree (`virtuna-ui-restrained`, branch `design/ui-restrained`) is the **UI design track** ‚Äî
the restrained-accent rebrand (de-Claude). It runs in PARALLEL with an engine/backend rework in a
separate worktree (`virtuna-engine-rework`, branch `rework/engine-core`). Stay in your lane to avoid
conflicts. The prior design batch (`design/ui-system`) is already merged to `main` ‚Äî branch off
`main`, not off the old branch.

## 1. Design system ‚Äî trust ONE source
- The **only** authoritative design references are `src/app/globals.css` (the `@theme` token
  block) and `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`. Read `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` before any visual work.
- **IGNORE these ‚Äî they are STALE** (they describe the retired Raycast/coral/glass system):
  `CLAUDE.md` "Raycast Design Language Rules" section, `BRAND-BIBLE.md`, `docs/tokens.md`,
  `docs/components.md`, `docs/design-specs.json`, `docs/usage-guidelines.md`,
  `docs/motion-guidelines.md`, `docs/brand/`.
- Current system = **flat-warm charcoal + cream text + MONOCHROME-by-default (accent near-zero) + matte**:
  - bg `#262624` (`--color-background`), cream text `#ece7de` (`--cream-primary`) ‚Äî **never `#fff`**
  - accent = **terracotta `#d97757`** (`--color-accent`), the brand mark (signal-red `#e23b2d` was trialed then reverted 2026-06-24 ‚Äî the de-Claude lever is the near-zero DOSAGE, not the hue). Never legacy `#FF7F50`.
  - **ACCENT DOSAGE IS LOCKED ‚Äî MONOCHROME BY DEFAULT, accent used REALLY sparingly, if at all.** A screen with ZERO accent is the norm, not a failure. Every accent use must be justified; aim for at most ONE accent element per view, often zero. The ONLY sanctioned uses: the single live presence/liveness dot, the lit constellation/SIM node, the brand mark. FORBIDDEN everywhere else ‚Äî primary buttons, icon buttons, skill pills, chevrons, placeholders, tabs, toggles, links, borders, charts, badges, large fills, hover states, and anything "to make it pop." Read "Accent dosage (LOCKED)" in `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` before touching color.
  - **Primary actions are NEUTRAL cream** ‚Äî use `--color-action` / `--color-action-foreground`, NOT the accent. (Composer send = cream button, dark glyph.)
  - accent-as-text on dark ‚Üí `--color-accent-text`; soft tint bg ‚Üí `--color-accent-soft`. Solid accent fill glyph ‚Üí `--color-accent-foreground` (cream).
  - `--color-accent` (brand terracotta) ‚âÝ `--color-error` (data/destructive red). Never conflate.
  - borders 6% (`rgba(255,255,255,0.06)`), hover 10%
  - **matte only**: no glass gradients, no glow, no white inset-shine. Flat + border + (rarely) `--shadow-float`.
  - Inter for all chrome; serif (`--font-serif`, Newsreader; Fraunces candidate) **only** for voice-moments (greeting/hero).
  - radius 4/6/8/12/16/20/24 ‚Äî cards 12, inputs/buttons 8.
  - **Identity is carried by the constellation/SIM motif + serif voice + copy**, since color is now quiet. Invest there.
- **Always consume tokens, never hardcode hex.** No `#FF7F50`, `#07080a`, `#18191a`, `#fff`, no raw `#d97757`/`#e23b2d` in components (use `--color-accent`).
- Keep `src/components/reading/__tests__/reskin-matte.test.ts` GREEN (guards against coral/glass).

## 2. File ownership ‚Äî DO NOT cross
- ‚úÖ **You own:** `src/components/**`, page-level styling/layout in `src/app/(app)/**` (NON-api),
  `src/app/globals.css`, design tokens, `src/types/design-tokens.ts`.
- ‚õî **Do NOT touch (engine track owns these):** `src/lib/**`, `src/app/api/**`, runners,
  engine, `supabase/**`, prompt/KC files. If a UI change seems to need a backend change,
  STOP and flag it ‚Äî don't edit backend here.

## 3. Coupled surfaces ‚Äî visual-only, don't change contracts
`AudienceLens`, the composer, and the thread skill-cards are being reworked on the engine side
(their data shape/props may change). For these you MAY restyle/relayout, but **do NOT change the
props/data contracts** they consume or the block schemas. Structural changes to these wait for
the engine rework ‚Äî coordinate first.

### 3a. ‚õî Engine-rework HOLD list ‚Äî do NOT edit (guaranteed merge conflict)
`rework/engine-core` (worktree `~/virtuna-engine-rework`) is 8 commits ahead of main, NOT yet
merged, and is actively rewriting these UI-lane files. Editing them here will conflict:
- `src/components/audience/calibration-flow.tsx`
- `src/components/audience/audience-reveal.tsx`
Leave both untouched until that branch lands on main. Everything else in `src/components/**` and
